==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Italian
<hw>I*tal"ian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>italien</ets>, It. <ets>italiano</ets>. Cf. <er>Italic</er>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to Italy, or to its people or language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Italian cloth</b></col> <cd>a light material of cotton
and worsted; -- called also <altname>farmer's satin</altname>.</cd> --
<col><b>Italian iron</b></col>, <cd>a heater for fluting frills.</cd> --
<col><b>Italian juice</b></col>, <cd>Calabrian liquorice.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Italian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Italian
<hw>I*tal"ian</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Italy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The language used in Italy, or by the
Italians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Italianate</ent>⟦br⟧
